JDR from Gauteng and Steernburg United from Western Cape have won promotion to the National First Division. The two sides will meet in the final of theÂ ABC Motsepe League playoffs which are underway in Cape Town. The competition kicked off on Wednesday at Erica Park in Cape Town with nine teams eyeing the whopping R1 million up for grabs and of course, a place in the second division of Mzansi football. Only two teams now, Steenberg from the Mother City, JDR Stars from Gauteng will lock horns in the final which is scheduled for Saturday. The final will determine who walks-away with the Million Rand cheque.   